originalText.text:
OK, everybody stop complaining that it's a skipped station; so are over 100 other stations not on a train that runs Express.

GET OVER IT!  If you can't, I'd suggest a car and the suburbs or another city frankly.

If you want Express and you are that much in a rush here are your choices:

Door to Door Car Service (Private, Uber/Lyft,...) Rent a ZipCar, Wave down a Taxi, Take a Bus, Walk 10 blocks North or South to An Express A or D train, walk 3 Avenues to a 2 or 3 Express Train,..

All of that off of my chest now, the "probable" reason that it is a local trains stop has more to do that the entire West side of the street, St. Nicholas Ave, (9th Avenue/Columbus Avenue for those living South of Central Park North -110th St) is St.Nicholas Park which runs the length from 128th st to 141 st .

Now that I have given a logical reason, can we all just enjoy that we don't need cars living here, can save carbon from the planet, do our cardio without having to look at stairmaster screens at the gym and never worry about a DUI or find parking when we are going out or coming home.

originalText.text: Hands down one of the worst stations in NYC. First its one of the stops that is skipped by express trains A and D. If you live in the area and need express you have to wait every 14 mins for C train or every 30 mins for B, and B only runs weekdays if you are lucky at works at all!! So to catch express you must either WALK up to 145th or down to 125th or take train and transfer at 125th which takes so much time by the time you do maybe two or three trains have already passed you. 135th always is being "fixed" seems like every weekend for 2 years the 135th station is being worked on so SOL, youre stuck trecking yourself to 145th or 125th ANYWAYS!! I've taken so many trains in the city, from Queens to Brooklyn and I havent been stuck in a station like 135th station and I regret moving to my 136th st. Apt. Because its given me so many headaches during rush hour.
